article.description: Shake Milton came off the bench to score 17 points, sparking SMU to an 85-50 win over Sam Houston State in the season opener for both schools Saturday night.
article.headline: Milton scores 17, SMU gallops past Sam Houston State, 85-50
article.linkText: Milton scores 17, SMU gallops past Sam Houston State, 85-50
article.story: DALLAS -- Shake Milton came off the bench to score 17 points, sparking SMU to an 85-50 win over Sam Houston State in the season opener for both schools Saturday night. SMU opened the game with a 9-0 run and held a 21-point lead at the break, 40-19. Sam Houston State held returning American Athletic Conference Player of the Year Nic Moore to just 8 points, but Ben Moore scored 15 points and grabbed eight rebounds and Keith Frazier added 13 points. SMU shot 63.3 percent from the field (31 of 49) and 7 of 14 from beyond the arc. The Bearkats were just 17 of 61 from the field (27.9 percent) and 6 of 27 from long range (22.2 percent). Dakarai Henderson scored 17 points to lead Sam Houston State. SMU enters the season after posting back-to-back 27-win seasons and winning the AAC regular season and tournament titles a year ago.
